item.description:
@I_Yaa_I wrote:

[quote=“pyroshell, post:2, topic:271867”]search for where you saw the “D” and change it back to what it was. other then that if it does work… go to client.java hit ctrl a
then right click and hit copy open notepad hit ctrl v and save it to desktop as client backup

so if you screw up again u just remove the client text and put in the backup text and recompile

its much safer =D hope i helped[br][br][size=1]Posted on: April 07, 2009, 09:49:12 pm[/size][hr]and u shouldnt be changing text in .class but in .java[/quote]

This error Occured nowhere Near the “D”
